The water regulator has backed down in its face-off with the supply industry over the introduction of the most far-reaching changes since privatisation.
But Ofwat has pledged that it will return to its longer-term goals of more fundamental deregulation once the forthcoming price review, setting charges for the next five years, is over.
One industry executive told The Times last night: “To mix our metaphors, Ofwat has offered an olive branch but also kicked the can down the road.”
